1
00:00:07,008 --> 00:00:08,824
[♪♪♪]

2
00:01:06,984 --> 00:01:09,451
[♪♪♪]

3
00:01:28,523 --> 00:01:30,083
Sawyer. Special Crimes Unit.

4
00:01:30,107 --> 00:01:31,757
[BEEPS]

5
00:01:42,052 --> 00:01:43,569
[TRUCK DOORS CLOSE]

6
00:01:45,472 --> 00:01:47,685
A late-night deposit, inspector?

7
00:01:47,709 --> 00:01:49,770
Yeah, some freshly laundered money

8
00:01:49,794 --> 00:01:51,394
we swept up in our latest raid.

9
00:01:53,664 --> 00:01:57,361
Won't those Intergang bums ever learn Turpin's first law?

10
00:01:57,385 --> 00:01:59,113
You play in my backyard,

11
00:01:59,137 --> 00:02:01,198
you play by my rules.

12
00:02:01,222 --> 00:02:02,571
Modest, isn't he?

13
00:02:13,101 --> 00:02:15,312
[LOUD BOOM] Please tell me that's thunder.

14
00:02:15,336 --> 00:02:17,536
Afraid not.

15
00:02:21,759 --> 00:02:24,376
I guess they think they can change the rules.

16
00:02:45,016 --> 00:02:46,248
[ALL YELL]

17
00:02:58,947 --> 00:03:00,841
This is Sawyer. All units.

18
00:03:00,865 --> 00:03:02,565
We need backup, now.

19
00:03:07,505 --> 00:03:08,704
[GASPS]

20
00:03:10,791 --> 00:03:12,023
[GRUNTS]

21
00:03:13,261 --> 00:03:14,393
Maggie!

22
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,813
[GRUNTING]

23
00:03:46,294 --> 00:03:48,606
Come back, you murdering scum!

24
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:49,840
<i>Come back!</i>

25
00:03:49,864 --> 00:03:52,181
It would serve him right if we did come back.

26
00:03:58,589 --> 00:03:59,605
THUG 1: Look out!

27
00:04:01,309 --> 00:04:02,708
[BOTH GRUNTING]

28
00:04:07,348 --> 00:04:09,131
Fire the nova bomb. Hurry!

29
00:04:16,324 --> 00:04:17,907
[GRUNTING]

30
00:04:32,790 --> 00:04:34,089
Fire!

31
00:04:39,479 --> 00:04:41,074
[EMITTING HIGH-PITCHED NOISE]

32
00:04:41,098 --> 00:04:42,098
[GROANING]

33
00:04:46,688 --> 00:04:48,253
[GROANING]

34
00:04:52,477 --> 00:04:54,309
[GROANING]

35
00:05:20,671 --> 00:05:22,265
[SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE]

36
00:05:22,289 --> 00:05:24,056
[PEOPLE MURMURING, MOANING]

37
00:05:25,810 --> 00:05:28,210
[WOMAN WEEPING]

38
00:05:31,432 --> 00:05:33,565
[SIRENS GROWING LOUDER]

39
00:05:43,177 --> 00:05:44,855
You shouldn't stay long, Dan.

40
00:05:44,879 --> 00:05:46,528
She's still very weak.

41
00:05:49,917 --> 00:05:50,894
Hi.

42
00:05:50,918 --> 00:05:52,968
Hi, yourself.

43
00:05:55,122 --> 00:05:56,900
Lying down on the job, huh?

44
00:05:56,924 --> 00:05:58,601
Some days you're the windshield,

45
00:05:58,625 --> 00:06:00,154
and some days you're the bug.

46
00:06:00,178 --> 00:06:03,407
Forget it. You'll be back busting my chops in no time.

47
00:06:03,431 --> 00:06:04,908
Any leads on the heist?

48
00:06:04,932 --> 00:06:06,693
Got our best people working on it.

49
00:06:06,717 --> 00:06:08,483
I... I mean, besides you.

50
00:06:10,037 --> 00:06:11,403
[GROANING]

51
00:06:12,823 --> 00:06:16,370
Maggie... I swear I'll find those filthy creeps.

52
00:06:16,394 --> 00:06:17,554
And when I do...

53
00:06:17,578 --> 00:06:20,290
Dan, these aren't simple street punks.

54
00:06:20,314 --> 00:06:22,492
Punks are punks, Maggie. I am gonna...!

55
00:06:22,516 --> 00:06:23,961
No!

56
00:06:23,985 --> 00:06:26,630
Promise me you'll keep that temper in check.

57
00:06:26,654 --> 00:06:28,553
Promise.

58
00:06:29,506 --> 00:06:30,850
You got it.

59
00:06:30,874 --> 00:06:32,107
Turpin's word.

60
00:06:34,211 --> 00:06:36,223
I'm gonna hold you to that, Dan,

61
00:06:36,247 --> 00:06:39,125
because it's all on you now.

62
00:06:39,149 --> 00:06:40,932
Yeah. I know.

63
00:06:44,638 --> 00:06:46,750
MAN: I tell you, it was beautiful, Bruno.

64
00:06:46,774 --> 00:06:47,751
We jacked the loot

65
00:06:47,775 --> 00:06:49,808
and left Superman kissing concrete.

66
00:06:52,546 --> 00:06:56,026
A few more jobs like this, and I'll own Metropolis.

67
00:06:56,050 --> 00:06:57,249
[BEEPING]

68
00:06:59,353 --> 00:07:02,320
Uh... I gotta take this call.

69
00:07:05,860 --> 00:07:06,970
You heard me.

70
00:07:06,994 --> 00:07:08,688
Out!

71
00:07:08,712 --> 00:07:10,512
[BEEPING FASTER]

72
00:07:21,892 --> 00:07:23,320
Darkseid.

73
00:07:23,344 --> 00:07:26,490
We tried out the tank, just like you said.

74
00:07:26,514 --> 00:07:28,358
<i>I did not return you to Earth</i>

75
00:07:28,382 --> 00:07:30,828
<i>so you could indulge in petty theft.</i>

76
00:07:30,852 --> 00:07:31,995
Petty?

77
00:07:32,019 --> 00:07:33,831
We cleared over 20 million!

78
00:07:33,855 --> 00:07:37,501
<i>I play for higher stakes.</i>

79
00:07:37,525 --> 00:07:39,391
Aah!

80
00:07:44,448 --> 00:07:47,077
<i>Do we understand each other?</i>

81
00:07:47,101 --> 00:07:48,661
[GULPS]

82
00:07:48,685 --> 00:07:50,180
<i>Good.</i>

83
00:07:50,204 --> 00:07:54,305
<i>Serve me well, Mannheim, and I'll make you a king.</i>

84
00:07:58,462 --> 00:07:59,789
[SIGHS]

85
00:07:59,813 --> 00:08:01,791
[REPORTERS CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

86
00:08:01,815 --> 00:08:03,560
So you're saying not even Superman

87
00:08:03,584 --> 00:08:05,195
could stop this thing?

88
00:08:05,219 --> 00:08:07,497
I'm saying we can't always expect one guy

89
00:08:07,521 --> 00:08:09,116
to save our sorry butts,

90
00:08:09,140 --> 00:08:10,367
even if he is Superman.

91
00:08:10,391 --> 00:08:12,652
This time, we'll have to tackle it ourselves.

92
00:08:12,676 --> 00:08:13,970
Good luck.

93
00:08:13,994 --> 00:08:16,423
[INDISTINCT CHATTER] REPORTER 1: Hey, Turpin!

94
00:08:16,447 --> 00:08:18,492
REPORTER 2: Dan,<i> Northstar Herald</i> here.

95
00:08:18,516 --> 00:08:20,077
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

96
00:08:20,101 --> 00:08:22,428
It almost looks... alien.

97
00:08:22,452 --> 00:08:23,530
Sure, Kent.

98
00:08:23,554 --> 00:08:25,904
Maybe it was a Martian strapped for cash.

99
00:08:31,545 --> 00:08:32,505
MAN 1: What is that?

100
00:08:32,529 --> 00:08:33,840
MAN 2: What's going on?

101
00:08:33,864 --> 00:08:35,775
Let's get outta here! WOMAN 1: Quick!

102
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:37,749
[CROWD YELLING]

103
00:08:45,009 --> 00:08:46,358
Whoa!

104
00:08:52,817 --> 00:08:54,366
[GROANING]

105
00:09:00,224 --> 00:09:01,256
Superman!

106
00:09:02,476 --> 00:09:06,973
Must warn... Superman.

107
00:09:06,997 --> 00:09:08,030
[GROANS]

108
00:09:17,825 --> 00:09:20,570
SUPERMAN: How's our mysterious visitor doing, Emil?

109
00:09:20,594 --> 00:09:23,240
His wounds are healing at a phenomenal rate.

110
00:09:23,264 --> 00:09:25,826
He's fully conscious, and in quite a rage to see...

111
00:09:25,850 --> 00:09:27,194
Superman!

112
00:09:27,218 --> 00:09:29,245
Get me Superman!

113
00:09:29,269 --> 00:09:30,564
Freeze, bucket-head!

114
00:09:30,588 --> 00:09:33,016
One more move, and you're back in intensive care.

115
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:34,122
Hold it, inspector!

116
00:09:35,225 --> 00:09:36,870
Everybody calm down.

117
00:09:36,894 --> 00:09:39,672
I didn't fight my way through a battalion of Parademons

118
00:09:39,696 --> 00:09:41,625
to be told to<i> calm down!</i>

119
00:09:41,649 --> 00:09:43,615
And they say I got a temper.

120
00:09:45,152 --> 00:09:48,131
You have me at a loss, Mr...

121
00:09:48,155 --> 00:09:50,783
My name is Orion.

122
00:09:50,807 --> 00:09:54,921
I fled from the fire-pits of Apokolips to warn you.

123
00:09:54,945 --> 00:09:56,139
He's coming.

124
00:09:56,163 --> 00:09:57,641
Who is?

125
00:09:57,665 --> 00:09:58,864
Darkseid.

126
00:10:03,236 --> 00:10:05,721
Mother Box can explain it better than I.

127
00:10:15,065 --> 00:10:17,783
She is a living computer connected to the Source.

128
00:10:23,406 --> 00:10:26,002
MOTHER BOX: <i>Let us begin at the beginning.</i>

129
00:10:26,026 --> 00:10:29,155
<i>What once was whole was split asunder.</i>

130
00:10:29,179 --> 00:10:32,392
<i>And in its place, there arose two worlds.</i>

131
00:10:32,416 --> 00:10:35,345
<i>Worlds as different as daylight and darkness,</i>

132
00:10:35,369 --> 00:10:36,819
<i>virtue and evil.</i>

133
00:10:38,488 --> 00:10:40,622
<i>One is called New Genesis.</i>

134
00:10:42,709 --> 00:10:45,744
<i>Unparalleled in its beauty...</i>

135
00:10:48,966 --> 00:10:53,284
<i>It is ruled by the wise and powerful Highfather.</i>

136
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:04,040
<i>The other is Apokolips, a ravaged wasteland</i>

137
00:11:04,064 --> 00:11:07,398
<i>ruled by the demonic and omnipotent Darkseid.</i>

138
00:11:12,005 --> 00:11:14,885
<i>He psychically feeds on the despair</i>

139
00:11:14,909 --> 00:11:17,442
<i>and misery of others.</i>

140
00:11:20,380 --> 00:11:22,576
<i>Because of their opposite natures,</i>

141
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:26,585
<i>these two worlds have been locked in eternal war.</i>

142
00:11:33,861 --> 00:11:37,891
<i>However, an uneasy truce was established</i>

143
00:11:37,915 --> 00:11:41,833
<i>when Darkseid and Highfather exchanged their infant sons.</i>

144
00:12:06,594 --> 00:12:08,788
<i>Unfortunately, this has not diminished.</i>

145
00:12:08,812 --> 00:12:10,507
<i>Darkseid's ambitions.</i>

146
00:12:10,531 --> 00:12:12,892
<i>For years he has searched the galaxies</i>

147
00:12:12,916 --> 00:12:15,428
<i>for the legendary Anti-Life Equation,</i>

148
00:12:15,452 --> 00:12:18,915
<i>a formula that would give him complete control</i>

149
00:12:18,939 --> 00:12:20,972
<i>over all living things.</i>

150
00:12:25,963 --> 00:12:28,258
<i>In his endless search,</i>

151
00:12:28,282 --> 00:12:31,310
<i>he has conquered and subjugated</i>

152
00:12:31,334 --> 00:12:33,835
<i>planet after planet.</i>

153
00:12:38,141 --> 00:12:39,936
Now he threatens Earth.

154
00:12:39,960 --> 00:12:42,455
He's already provided human agents

155
00:12:42,479 --> 00:12:44,024
with Apokoliptic weaponry.

156
00:12:44,048 --> 00:12:45,274
The hover tank?

157
00:12:45,298 --> 00:12:47,343
Is just a prelude. [CELL PHONE RINGING]

158
00:12:47,367 --> 00:12:48,783
Turpin.

159
00:12:49,986 --> 00:12:51,565
I'm here to offer my assistance

160
00:12:51,589 --> 00:12:53,583
in the coming battle.

161
00:12:53,607 --> 00:12:55,718
Well, strap on your six-gun, space cowboy.

162
00:12:55,742 --> 00:12:58,354
Your playmates are attacking Sinnott Air Force Base.

163
00:12:58,378 --> 00:13:00,345
[SIRENS WAILING]

164
00:13:03,734 --> 00:13:04,799
[TIRES SCREECH]

165
00:13:06,854 --> 00:13:08,064
What? Take cover!

166
00:13:08,088 --> 00:13:09,988
MAN: Down! MAN 2: Go, go, go!

167
00:13:25,089 --> 00:13:26,316
Blue Leader One,

168
00:13:26,340 --> 00:13:28,284
I just lost contact with the tower.

169
00:13:28,308 --> 00:13:29,319
Cover me.

170
00:13:29,343 --> 00:13:30,475
Roger.

171
00:13:35,415 --> 00:13:37,026
Locked on target.

172
00:13:37,050 --> 00:13:38,066
Fire!

173
00:13:56,820 --> 00:13:58,353
[MEN PANTING]

174
00:14:06,229 --> 00:14:07,329
[GRUNTING]

175
00:14:12,636 --> 00:14:15,036
Scratch one hero.

176
00:14:18,375 --> 00:14:19,375
[YELLING]

177
00:14:29,868 --> 00:14:32,034
[YELLING, GROANING]

178
00:14:41,530 --> 00:14:43,429
By the Source.

179
00:14:58,747 --> 00:15:00,063
[BOTH YELLING]

180
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:13,977
[GROANS]

181
00:15:17,599 --> 00:15:19,031
Help! Get us outta here!

182
00:15:20,552 --> 00:15:21,552
[GRUNTING]

183
00:15:49,164 --> 00:15:50,897
This ain't happening.

184
00:15:52,467 --> 00:15:54,533
[GROANS]

185
00:15:56,654 --> 00:15:59,417
<i>I take it the battle is not going well.</i>

186
00:15:59,441 --> 00:16:00,785
It's not my fault.

187
00:16:00,809 --> 00:16:03,009
It's that new guy.

188
00:16:12,503 --> 00:16:13,970
[GRUNTING]

189
00:16:32,707 --> 00:16:34,151
<i>Orion.</i>

190
00:16:34,175 --> 00:16:36,087
You know that creep?

191
00:16:36,111 --> 00:16:37,671
<i>Doesn't matter.</i>

192
00:16:37,695 --> 00:16:40,791
<i>We're ready to begin phase two, Mr. Mannheim.</i>

193
00:16:40,815 --> 00:16:42,243
You mean the power plant?

194
00:16:42,267 --> 00:16:43,661
Now?

195
00:16:43,685 --> 00:16:45,218
Now.

196
00:17:03,922 --> 00:17:04,999
Who...? Who are you?

197
00:17:05,023 --> 00:17:05,984
How did you...?

198
00:17:06,008 --> 00:17:08,619
So many questions, so little time.

199
00:17:08,643 --> 00:17:09,809
[SCREAMS]

200
00:17:10,662 --> 00:17:12,495
[SIRENS WAILING]

201
00:17:15,150 --> 00:17:16,282
[BRAKES SCREECH]

202
00:17:18,837 --> 00:17:20,586
[FIRE TRUCK HORN HONKING]

203
00:17:31,116 --> 00:17:32,482
[GRUNTING]

204
00:17:33,568 --> 00:17:35,863
You know, Superman, I play a pretty good game,

205
00:17:35,887 --> 00:17:37,648
but, uh, not in this league.

206
00:17:37,672 --> 00:17:40,051
I don't know what we would have done without you.

207
00:17:40,075 --> 00:17:41,757
I'm not the one to thank.

208
00:17:49,251 --> 00:17:52,146
It was a good thing you showed up, Orion.

209
00:17:52,170 --> 00:17:53,481
It was too easy.

210
00:17:53,505 --> 00:17:56,150
Oh, yeah. A real walk in the park.

211
00:17:56,174 --> 00:17:57,568
Don't mock me.

212
00:17:57,592 --> 00:18:01,038
Darkseid will consider this a minor setback, if that.

213
00:18:01,062 --> 00:18:02,907
I know how he thinks.

214
00:18:02,931 --> 00:18:04,409
Oh?

215
00:18:04,433 --> 00:18:06,310
Yes.

216
00:18:06,334 --> 00:18:07,350
I'm his son.

217
00:18:09,187 --> 00:18:11,014
I was the infant Darkseid gave up

218
00:18:11,038 --> 00:18:13,584
to pay for his... uneasy truce.

219
00:18:13,608 --> 00:18:14,752
I'm sorry.

220
00:18:14,776 --> 00:18:16,170
I had no idea.

221
00:18:16,194 --> 00:18:17,705
It doesn't matter.

222
00:18:17,729 --> 00:18:19,890
Right now, I must return to New Genesis

223
00:18:19,914 --> 00:18:22,449
and report Darkseid's latest aggressions.

224
00:18:26,455 --> 00:18:30,290
You may use this to contact me when you need further help.

225
00:18:33,345 --> 00:18:35,244
And you will need it.

226
00:18:45,056 --> 00:18:46,356
[BEEPING]

227
00:18:48,326 --> 00:18:51,305
BRUNO: The island's been evacuated, just like you ordered.

228
00:18:51,329 --> 00:18:53,708
And the incendiary's all set to take out

229
00:18:53,732 --> 00:18:55,331
the reactor's cooling system.

230
00:19:05,627 --> 00:19:07,371
There it goes.

231
00:19:07,395 --> 00:19:08,573
You know, Darkseid,

232
00:19:08,597 --> 00:19:11,263
you and me, we make a great team.

233
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:14,311
<i>Hmm. Indeed.</i>

234
00:19:14,335 --> 00:19:16,614
<i>You have served me well, Mr. Mannheim.</i>

235
00:19:16,638 --> 00:19:19,389
<i>And now, farewell.</i>

236
00:19:20,392 --> 00:19:21,591
Ah?

237
00:19:23,228 --> 00:19:25,539
What gives? What about me?

238
00:19:25,563 --> 00:19:27,709
You promised you'd make me a king!

239
00:19:27,733 --> 00:19:29,443
<i>And so you are.</i>

240
00:19:29,467 --> 00:19:30,950
<i>The king of fools.</i>

241
00:19:31,886 --> 00:19:33,547
Darkseid?

242
00:19:33,571 --> 00:19:35,349
Darkseid.

243
00:19:35,373 --> 00:19:37,172
No!

244
00:19:41,630 --> 00:19:43,691
Gotta be a kill switch.

245
00:19:43,715 --> 00:19:44,759
[YELLS]

246
00:19:44,783 --> 00:19:45,815
[MOANS]

247
00:19:49,721 --> 00:19:50,681
Aah!

248
00:19:50,705 --> 00:19:52,672
[GRUNTING]

249
00:20:02,467 --> 00:20:04,562
[SPLUTTERING]

250
00:20:04,586 --> 00:20:06,252
Come on.

251
00:20:11,793 --> 00:20:13,404
[GRUNTING]

252
00:20:13,428 --> 00:20:14,894
[RUMBLING] Yes!

253
00:20:22,420 --> 00:20:24,465
[EXPLOSION]

254
00:20:24,489 --> 00:20:25,888
Holy Hannah!

255
00:20:31,129 --> 00:20:33,507
Orion was right.

256
00:20:33,531 --> 00:20:34,631
It isn't over.

257
00:20:44,425 --> 00:20:46,491
[♪♪♪]

